# Ager – Manual Test Cases

**Project:** Ager Property Management System  
**Base URL:** `http://localhost:8000`  
**Date:** 2026-03-02  
**Test Environment:** Local (SQLite in-memory for unit tests; MySQL for manual testing)

> **Legend** — Mark each result as: ✅ Pass | ❌ Fail | ⏭ Skip

---

## Module 1 — Authentication

| ID | Test Case | Steps | Expected Result | Result |
|----|-----------|-------|-----------------|--------|
| AUTH-01 | Login with valid credentials | 1. Go to `/login`<br>2. Enter valid email & password<br>3. Click **Login** | Redirected to `/dashboard`. Session is active. | |
| AUTH-02 | Login with invalid password | 1. Go to `/login`<br>2. Enter valid email + wrong password<br>3. Click **Login** | Error message shown: "These credentials do not match our records." | |
| AUTH-03 | Login with empty fields | 1. Go to `/login`<br>2. Leave both fields empty<br>3. Click **Login** | Validation errors shown for email and password fields. | |
| AUTH-04 | Logout | 1. Log in as any user<br>2. Click **Logout** | Redirected to `/login`. Session is destroyed. Accessing `/dashboard` redirects back to `/login`. | |
| AUTH-05 | Guest is redirected on protected page | 1. Without logging in, visit `/buildings` | Redirected to `/login`. | |
| AUTH-06 | Register new user (via registration form) | 1. Go to `/register`<br>2. Fill name, email, password, confirm password<br>3. Click **Register** | New user account created. Redirected to `/dashboard`. | |
| AUTH-07 | Password reset – request link | 1. Go to `/forgot-password`<br>2. Enter registered email<br>3. Click **Send Reset Link** | Success message shown. Reset email sent. | |
| AUTH-08 | Password reset – use token | 1. Click link from reset email<br>2. Enter new password + confirmation<br>3. Submit | Password changed. Redirected to `/login`. Can log in with new password. | |
| AUTH-09 | Email verification prompt | 1. Register a new user<br>2. Navigate to verification-required area | Prompt shown to verify email. Verification email sent. | |

---

## Module 2 — Dashboard

| ID | Test Case | Steps | Expected Result | Result |
|----|-----------|-------|-----------------|--------|
| DASH-01 | Dashboard loads correctly | 1. Log in as owner<br>2. Visit `/dashboard` | Page renders. Shows: Total Buildings, Total Units, Rented Units, Vacant Units, Active Contracts. | |
| DASH-02 | Monthly income widget | 1. Ensure at least one payment exists this month<br>2. Visit `/dashboard` | "This Month's Income" displays the correct summed amount. | |
| DASH-03 | Overdue schedules count | 1. Ensure at least one overdue rent schedule exists<br>2. Visit `/dashboard` | Overdue count and total overdue amount are displayed correctly. | |
| DASH-04 | Contracts ending soon | 1. Create a contract with an end date within the next 30 days<br>2. Visit `/dashboard` | The contract appears in the "Ending Soon" list with tenant name and unit. | |
| DASH-05 | Monthly income chart | 1. Visit `/dashboard` | A bar/line chart shows the last 6 months of income with correct month labels. | |

---

## Module 3 — Buildings

| ID | Test Case | Steps | Expected Result | Result |
|----|-----------|-------|-----------------|--------|
| BLDG-01 | List all buildings | 1. Log in<br>2. Go to `/buildings` | All buildings listed with unit counts (total, active, vacant). Paginated at 15. | |
| BLDG-02 | Create building – valid data | 1. Go to `/buildings/create`<br>2. Fill: Name, City, Address, Late Penalty Type = Percent, Value = 5<br>3. Submit | Redirected to the new building's detail page. Success flash message shown. Building visible in list. | |
| BLDG-03 | Create building – name required | 1. Go to `/buildings/create`<br>2. Leave **Name** empty<br>3. Submit | Validation error: "The name field is required." Form not submitted. | |
| BLDG-04 | View building detail | 1. Click on a building name from the list | Building detail page shows building info and a list of its units (with tenant names for rented units). | |
| BLDG-05 | Edit building | 1. Open a building detail<br>2. Click **Edit**<br>3. Change name<br>4. Submit | Redirected back to building detail. Updated name shown. Success message visible. | |
| BLDG-06 | Delete building | 1. Open a building<br>2. Click **Delete** / confirm deletion | Building removed from list. Visit `/buildings` confirms it no longer appears (soft-deleted). | |
| BLDG-07 | Audit log on create | 1. Create a new building as an authenticated user<br>2. Visit `/audit-log` | A `building.created` entry appears with the correct user and building ID. | |

---

## Module 4 — Units

| ID | Test Case | Steps | Expected Result | Result |
|----|-----------|-------|-----------------|--------|
| UNIT-01 | List all units | 1. Go to `/units` | All units listed with building name and status. Paginated at 20. | |
| UNIT-02 | Filter by building | 1. Go to `/units`<br>2. Select a building from the filter<br>3. Submit | Only units belonging to that building are shown. | |
| UNIT-03 | Filter by status | 1. Go to `/units`<br>2. Select status = **Vacant**<br>3. Submit | Only vacant units shown. | |
| UNIT-04 | Filter by type | 1. Go to `/units`<br>2. Choose a unit type<br>3. Submit | Only units of that type shown. | |
| UNIT-05 | Create unit – valid | 1. Go to `/units/create`<br>2. Select a building, enter unit number, type, floor, area<br>3. Submit | Redirected to unit detail. Success message shown. Unit appears in list. | |
| UNIT-06 | Create unit – required fields missing | 1. Go to `/units/create` and submit empty form | Validation errors for required fields. | |
| UNIT-07 | View unit detail | 1. Click a unit from the list | Unit detail page shows: building, contracts history, maintenance requests. | |
| UNIT-08 | Edit unit | 1. Open a unit<br>2. Click **Edit**<br>3. Change floor number<br>4. Submit | Updated data shown on detail page. Success message. | |
| UNIT-09 | Delete unit | 1. Open a unit (that has no active contract)<br>2. Click **Delete** | Unit removed. Success message. Redirected to `/units`. | |
| UNIT-10 | Unit status auto-changes to Rented | 1. Create a contract for a **Vacant** unit<br>2. Revisit the unit detail | Unit status changed to **Rented**. | |

