## Module 6 — Contracts

| ID | Test Case | Steps | Expected Result | Result |
|----|-----------|-------|-----------------|--------|
| CONT-01 | List contracts | 1. Go to `/contracts` | All contracts with tenant, unit, building, and status shown. Paginated at 20. | |
| CONT-02 | Filter by status | 1. Go to `/contracts`<br>2. Select **Active** from status filter | Only active contracts shown. | |
| CONT-03 | Filter by expired | 1. Go to `/contracts`<br>2. Select **Expired** | Contracts whose end date has passed but are still active shown. | |
| CONT-04 | Filter by building | 1. Go to `/contracts`<br>2. Select a building from filter | Only contracts for units in that building shown. | |
| CONT-05 | Create contract – monthly | 1. Go to `/contracts/create`<br>2. Select a vacant unit and a tenant<br>3. Set start date, end date, rent amount, payment frequency = **Monthly**<br>4. Submit | Contract created. Rent schedule generated (one row per month). Redirected to contract detail. | |
| CONT-06 | Create contract – quarterly | Same as CONT-05 but frequency = **Quarterly** | Rent schedule has one row every 3 months. | |
| CONT-07 | Create contract – yearly | Same as CONT-05 but frequency = **Yearly** | Rent schedule has one row per year. | |
| CONT-08 | Create contract – with file upload | 1. Fill the create form<br>2. Attach a PDF file<br>3. Submit | Contract saved with file. File link visible on detail page. | |
| CONT-09 | Create contract – annual increase (percent) | 1. Set annual increase type = **Percent**, value = 10<br>2. Submit (multi-year contract) | Rent for year 2+ is 10% higher in the schedule. | |
| CONT-10 | Create contract – annual increase (fixed) | 1. Set annual increase type = **Fixed**, value = 500<br>2. Submit | Rent for year 2+ is 500 higher. | |
| CONT-11 | View contract detail | 1. Open a contract | Shows: tenant, unit/building, all payment schedules, payments made, additional charges. | |
| CONT-12 | Edit contract | 1. Open a contract → **Edit**<br>2. Change the deposit amount<br>3. Submit | Updated. Redirected to detail. Success message. | |
| CONT-13 | Terminate contract – keep deposit | 1. Open an active contract<br>2. Click **Terminate**<br>3. Select deposit action = **Keep**<br>4. Confirm | Contract status = **Terminated**. Deposit kept. Unit status reverts to **Vacant**. | |
| CONT-14 | Terminate contract – refund deposit | 1. Open an active contract<br>2. Click **Terminate**<br>3. Select deposit action = **Refund**, enter amount<br>4. Confirm | Contract terminated. Refund recorded. Unit becomes **Vacant**. | |
| CONT-15 | Delete contract | 1. Open a contract → **Delete** | Contract removed. Redirected to `/contracts`. | |

---

## Module 7 — Rent Schedules

| ID | Test Case | Steps | Expected Result | Result |
|----|-----------|-------|-----------------|--------|
| RENT-01 | View rent schedule list | 1. Go to `/rent-schedules` | All schedule entries listed with status (pending, paid, overdue, partial). | |
| RENT-02 | View single schedule | 1. Click a schedule entry | Detail page shows: due date, final amount, paid amount, status, any penalty applied. | |
| RENT-03 | Overdue status applied automatically | 1. Ensure a schedule's due date is in the past and it is unpaid<br>2. Trigger the penalty service (or wait for scheduled job)<br>3. Revisit the schedule | Status changed to **Overdue**. Penalty amount applied if penalty type is set. | |
| RENT-04 | Percent late penalty | 1. Configure building with 5% late penalty<br>2. Let a schedule become overdue<br>3. View the schedule | `final_amount` = original amount × 1.05. | |
| RENT-05 | Fixed late penalty | 1. Configure building with fixed 200 penalty<br>2. Let a schedule become overdue | `final_amount` = original amount + 200. | |
| RENT-06 | No penalty when type is none | 1. Configure building with penalty type = **None**<br>2. Let a schedule become overdue | `final_amount` unchanged. Status = **Overdue**. | |

