## Module 9 — Maintenance

| ID | Test Case | Steps | Expected Result | Result |
|----|-----------|-------|-----------------|--------|
| MAINT-01 | List maintenance requests | 1. Go to `/maintenance` | All requests shown with unit, building, status. Paginated at 20. | |
| MAINT-02 | Filter by status | 1. Go to `/maintenance`<br>2. Select **Pending** filter | Only pending requests shown. | |
| MAINT-03 | Create maintenance request | 1. Go to `/maintenance/create`<br>2. Select a unit, enter description<br>3. Submit | Request saved with status **Pending**. Redirected to maintenance list. Success message. | |
| MAINT-04 | Create request – description required | 1. Submit without description | Validation error shown. | |
| MAINT-05 | View maintenance detail | 1. Click a maintenance request | Detail shows: unit, building, assigned user, description, cost, dates, status. | |
| MAINT-06 | Update maintenance – assign user | 1. Open a request → **Edit**<br>2. Assign to a user<br>3. Set status = **In Progress**<br>4. Submit | Status updated. Assigned user shown on detail. Success message. | |
| MAINT-07 | Update maintenance – mark completed | 1. Open an in-progress request → **Edit**<br>2. Set status = **Completed**, enter cost, finished date<br>3. Submit | Status = **Completed**. Cost and dates saved. | |
| MAINT-08 | Cancel maintenance request | 1. Open a request → **Edit**<br>2. Set status = **Cancelled**<br>3. Submit | Status = **Cancelled**. Visible on detail page. | |

